By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The total confirmed cases of COVID-19 had risen to 63,508 in Nigeria as the Centre for Disease Control yesterday confirmed that 180 new infections were recorded. However, the report released via twitter handle further informed that a total of 59,748 have been discharged after they were certified to have tested negative after treatment. The health agency confirmed that 1,155 lives had been lost to COVID-19 related complications since the index case in Nigeria. According to the report, the 180 new cases were recorded from 14 States of the federation including FCT as follows: Lagos-87Oyo-51FCT-12Plateau-10Edo-4Ekiti-3Ogun-3Bauchi-2Kaduna-2Niger-2Kano-1Ondo-1Osun-1Rivers-1 See the state by state breakdown of total confirmed cases across the 36 states of the Federation, By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Thursday said that it has confirmed 354 new cases of COVID-19 infection, bringing the total confirmed cases to 45,244. The health agency reported that the 354 new infections were recorded in 17 out of the 36… August 7, 2020 In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -   The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Wednesday said it has confirmed 111 new cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria. This new cases, it said, brought total Confirmed COVID-19 infections in Nigeria to 57,724 out of which 48,985 patients have been discharged. According to… September 24, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Nigeria's confirmed COVID-19 infections figure shrunk to  58 new cases on Sunday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has said. According to the report released by the NCDC, the newly recorded cases brought the total confirmed cases to 59,345 out of which… October 5, 2020 In "Top Stories"